President Donald J. Trump and First Lady Melania Trump hosted their first Congressional Picnic on the South Lawn of the White House. The event, styled after President Trump's hometown, New York City, had a Central Park theme. Vice President Mike Pence and Mrs. Karen Pence were also in attendance. Vice President Pence emphasized the importance of family and leaving politics outside the gate during the picnic. President Trump gave an update on Congressman Steve Scalise's recovery and thanked the special agents for their lifesaving actions. He also expressed his hope for unity and cooperation in Congress to create an optimistic future for all Americans. After his remarks, the President spent time with the families and Congressmen in attendance.